at playing a Cleric either.  I have seen a few people complain about the changes to healing made by Verant.  I am creating this post to offer some solutions I have found to the problem, and ask that any other suggestions be made.<br>
<br>
This obviously isn't a perfect guide, but let's do our best.<br>
<br>
Single Group situations:<br>
I spend the vast majority of my time in single groups with a Warrior and Enchanter with the rest of the spots filled in with other classes.  Having a these other two classes makes managing the aggro caused from healing a much easier task.  The biggest fear, obviously, is having the Cleric getting aggro'd immediately following a CH on the Warrior.  This is easily solved by having the Enchanter stun the mob several times immediatly before and after the CH happens.  This gives time for the Cleric or Enchanter to wipe the hate list if/when needed.  At other times, I find that casting Root immediately before the CH can give more time for the taunters to keep the mob off me.<br>
<br>
In single group situations, I have my 8 spell slots filled with Remedy, Celestial Healing, Complete Heal, Atone, Stun, Holy Might, Divine Barrier, and Divine Aura.  I have the stun spells and the root spells scribed on the same page in my spell book so I can swap them out quickly.<br>
<br>
<br>
Multiple Group Situations:<br>
In multiple group raids, I find that using the above techniques can hamper the efforts of the raid.  We need to find other ways of dealing with the hate list.  Having a large number of taunting classes makes the amount of time oyu are at the top of the hate list minimal.  The amount of time you need to put up with a mob beating on you is much smaller.  Conversely, the damage being done to you by one of these mobs is much higher.<br>
<br>
I find that, as a Cleric, I have little use for an /assist button.  Its really only needed as an information source to see how close to death the engaged mob is.  I have replaced this key with a /target key.  I have target keys for the other Clerics on the raid (also Enchanters).  In tough fights, I hit that target key(s) as many times as I can to check on the health of the other Cleric.  Getting communication from these other Clerics (when they are healing, etc.) only adds minimal battle spam and can help you ensure that the other Clerics stay alive.<br>
<br>
<br>
There are more I can list out, but I'd like to see what other Clerics do. <p>Peace,<BR>
