<br>
I do switch out and mem stuns (three if I can manage the slots, Stun/HolyMight/Force) if the puller calls out caster mobs or other spellcasting mobs and there is no enchanter in group.  Those take the longest to refresh therefore have to mem them early or as quickly as possible.<br>
<br>
I always have two slots of heals, and sometimes three (CH) depending on the make-up of the group.  Those top three heals, since I don't have Remedy or Celestial Healing yet, are usually my two best heals (Greater Heal for casters at this point, and Superior Heal) and Complete Healing.<br>
<br>
Then of course, Atone, DA, and DB, and have to admit, I'm shocked at the clerics who don't at least have their Divines memmed, because they are all very very handy to have when you need to clear aggro, keep yourself from death, and heal your group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
